 percent to close at N13.6 billion from N11.8 billion recorded in H1’18, whilst gross earnings increased by 12.3 percent to N103.7 billion from N92.3 billion. Phyno shuts down Enugu for Hi-life fest semi-final(Opens in a new browser tab) Commenting on the results, Fidelity Bank CEO, Mr. Nnamdi Okonkwo, expressed delight with the bank’s financial performance. According to Okonkwo, the bank remained focused on the execution of its medium-term strategic goals and targets for the 2019 financial year whilst promising that the bank would continue to sustain the momentum and deliver another strong set of results for the nine months, 2019. Vanguard FIDELITY Bank Plc’s profit before tax rose 34 percent to N6.7 billion in the first quarter ending March 2019 (Q1’19). April 29, 2019 In "Business" Fidelity Bank Plc has recorded 27.3 percent growth in its profit before tax (PBT) for the first half ended June 30,  2018 (H1’18) to N13 billion from N10.2 billion. September 27, 2018 In "News" FIDELITY Bank Plc has said that its profit before tax (PBT) grew by 30.6 percent to N25.1 billion in the financial year ended December 31, 2018 from N19.2 billion in the previous year. April 1, 2019 In "Business"